quote: "What is to be sung, "
subject: The Haiku Influence on Modern Nature Poetry (1910s–1920s)
permalink: /The Haiku Influence on Modern Nature Poetry (1910s–1920s)/HD/HD - What Is to Be Sung
---

What is to be sung, 
Shall be a river; 
What is to be won, 
A flower, shortening its span, 
Embellishing curves of hills 
Waving in gentle breath; 
It can be remembered,
In night’s soft unfoldings, 
Where fallen leaves flutter—
Let me rise to the sky and rest!

- HD
